goals.question: What is the distribution of income across different countries?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the spread of income across different countries and identify any outliers.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between income and health?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of income vs health
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is any correlation between income and health, and if so, the strength and direction of the correlation.

goals.question: What is the distribution of population across different regions?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of population by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us understand the population distribution across different regions and identify any regions with significantly higher or lower population than others.

goals.question: What is the average income and health of countries in each region?
goals.visualization: Grouped bar chart of average income and health by region
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us compare the average income and health of countries in each region and identify any regions with significantly higher or lower average income or health than others.

goals.question: What is the relationship between income, health, and population?
goals.visualization: 3D scatter plot of income, health, and population
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify any patterns or relationships between income, health, and population, and if so, the strength and direction of the relationships.

code:
```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.boxplot(data['income'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of income across different countries?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Income')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['income'], data['health'])
    plt.xlabel('Income')
    plt.ylabel('Health')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between income and health?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').sum().reset_index()
    plt.bar(data['region'], data['population'], color=['#1f77b4', '#ff7f0e', '#2ca02c', '#d62728', '#9467bd', '#8c564b'])
    plt.title('What is the distribution of population across different regions?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Population')
    plt.xlabel('Region')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.groupby('region').mean().reset_index()
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.bar(data['region'], data['income'], color='blue', label='Income')
    ax.bar(data['region'], data['health'], color='green', label='Health')
    ax.set_xlabel('Region')
    ax.set_ylabel('Average')
    ax.set_title('What is the average income and health of countries in each region?')
    ax.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

```
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from mpl_toolkits.mplot3d import Axes3D

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig = plt.figure()
    ax = fig.add_subplot(111, projection='3d')
    ax.scatter(data['income'], data['health'], data['population'], c='blue', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Income')
    ax.set_ylabel('Health')
    ax.set_zlabel('Population')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between income, health, and population?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```
